    "# Ethics & Privacy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The data collected for this study comes from publicly available datasets, using data from the CDC’s National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey (NHANES). Data collected are shown anonymously and have been provided informed consent from participants, allowing the studies to proceed within established privacy guidelines. \n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset’s sampling may introduce potential biases, retrieving data from certain subpopulations may be less representative and those with limited healthcare access or from other socioeconomic factors could be underrepresented. This underrepresentation can affect a fair analysis, as trends in mental health and alcohol use may differ across different demographic groups. \n",
    "\n",
    "To address these biases, we aim to acknowledge the demographic limitations and indicate that the trends that we study do not fully reveal the experiences of all U.S. adults. Studying the dataset closely, we will identify the gaps that could influence connections/relationships that we find between depression and alcohol use frequency during COVID and post-COVID."
   ]
